the same language and were talking the same way versus to working at Moderna, where you kind of

00:18:51.959 --> 00:18:59.640
have to interface with a whole different group of people, say biologists, data scientists,

00:19:00.359 --> 00:19:09.000
a very diverse kind of group of people, assuming that it was less diverse in the sense of having

00:19:09.000 --> 00:19:14.119
more biostatisticians in your previous role? And kind of what challenges did you have and

00:19:14.119 --> 00:19:18.359
kind of how did you deal with that? Okay. Yeah, I love that question.

00:19:19.319 --> 00:19:27.160
I think it's an awesome part about the clinical trial world is that you do get to interface with

00:19:27.160 --> 00:19:35.239
people in so many different roles. And I would say that at my previous position, I did interface

00:19:35.239 --> 00:19:42.760
with a lot of different types of people already. And so maybe that was good preparation, working

00:19:42.760 --> 00:19:50.680
with clinicians on the trial. I even used to have phone calls with people at the sites. That was

