what's the limiting principle for how much interactivity to give people? Because I kind

00:32:30.599 --> 00:32:35.560
of found that there are two sides to that continuum. One, you can just keep building

00:32:35.560 --> 00:32:40.280
the app and building the app and adding more functionality. But you want to deliver it.

00:32:41.079 --> 00:32:45.319
And then the more content you add, the more functionality you add to it, the more possibility

00:32:45.719 --> 00:32:48.680
someone else pointed out that there's a possibility that people are going to

00:32:49.560 --> 00:32:55.959
derive insights that aren't necessarily true or meaningful. But then on the flip side,

00:32:55.959 --> 00:32:59.319
you know that the one thing you don't implement is the thing you're going to get asked for.

00:33:00.040 --> 00:33:05.479
So where do you draw the line on what to do and what to leave out?

00:33:06.439 --> 00:33:17.000
That's a big question. It's difficult to nail down. I think in my particular realm of things,

00:33:18.119 --> 00:33:25.000
I definitely think about it along the lines of where a study is progressing. So

00:33:26.199 --> 00:33:32.760
in the early, early phases of a clinical trial, or even preclinical, things can be

00:33:33.000 --> 00:33:40.520
much more exploratory. And so when exploratory is the goal, hypothesis generating is the goal,

00:33:42.040 --> 00:33:53.000
you know, go crazy and put a disclaimer that, you know, there are things discoverable here that need

00:33:53.000 --> 00:34:02.599
to be proven outside of this application. And then when you work your way down to, you know,

00:34:03.400 --> 00:34:11.399
questions that are more formulated, a researcher has really provided the question they're trying

00:34:11.399 --> 00:34:18.600
to answer. That's where I would think about limiting it and trying to really just answer

00:34:18.600 --> 00:34:26.040
the question that's being asked and limit the back and forth. Because, you know, there's a

00:34:26.040 --> 00:34:32.280
whole theory behind this. But when you're in phase three of a clinical trial, the question should be

00:34:33.000 --> 00:34:40.439
laid out and the question should be answerable. And that upholds the entire integrity of the trial.

00:34:40.439 --> 00:34:45.479
So that's kind of how I think about it. No, that's great. Thank you. I also really

