open source. So yeah, your question had a lot of different parts again. So as far as our team

00:48:42.679 --> 00:48:49.639
using Pharmaverse, so a little background for non-pharma people, Pharmaverse is a collection

00:48:49.639 --> 00:48:59.719
of packages contributed to by all different pharma companies as well as CROs. And the aim of the

00:48:59.719 --> 00:49:06.360
Pharmaverse packages is largely to do with submission. So actually putting a drug in front

00:49:06.360 --> 00:49:15.080
of the FDA for approval. And that is not where my group is using open source software at this time.

00:49:15.879 --> 00:49:22.120
We're very much keeping our eyes and ears open to it. And if that's something you're interested in

00:49:22.120 --> 00:49:29.399
and you haven't yet watched Nova Nordic's YouTube video, someone can put it in the chat. That's like

